SUMMARY:Houston Restaurant Weeks 2026
DESCRIPTION:Houston Restaurant Weeks is the largest annual fundraiser for America’s largest food bank\, the Houston Food Bank. It’s a month-long dining extravaganza featuring specially priced lunches\, brunches\, and dinners at restaurants from The Woodlands to Galveston. \nParticipating restaurants make donations based on how many prix fixe brunches\, lunches\, and dinners they sell during the event. Diners are not solicited for donations. \nBeginning July 15\, diners can visit HoustonRestaurantWeeks.com to view the 2026 list of restaurants that have committed to participate\, along with their HRW menus. \nThe event includes restaurants located in Harris\, Galveston\, and Montgomery counties. The Galveston County Food Bank and Montgomery County Food Bank are part of the Houston Food Bank’s Affiliate Food Banks. The Houston Food Bank provides food to these smaller food banks\, which in turn distribute the food to hunger relief charities in a portion of HFB’s service area. The Houston Food Bank certifies that their Affiliate Food Banks meet Feeding America standards.
URL:https://www.houstonfoodbank.org/upcomingevent/houston-restaurant-weeks-2026/
CATEGORIES:Eat Drink HTX,FEATURED,Fund Drive,Houston Restaurant Weeks
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.houstonfoodbank.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/HRW2026-1200x900-2.jpg
END:VEVENT
